        jLabel4.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12));
        jLabel4.setText("<html>\n<b>(1)</b> The measure of a product is the product of the measures. We used this\nin our example, where [ma] = [m][a].<br><br>\n<b>(2)</b> Similarly, we can exponentiate dimensions. For example, √m = √[m] = [M]<sup>1/2</sup><br><br>\n<b>(3)</b> We can only add terms that have the same units of measure. For example,\nwe cannot add meters to minutes.<br><br>\n<b>(4)</b> Physical relationships must be dimensionally consistent (for example, the\nlaws of physics).\n\n</html>");
        jLabel4.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        jLabel4.setBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createTitledBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createLineBorder(new java.awt.Color(0, 0, 0))));
