        jLabel9.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 13));
        jLabel9.setText("<html>\n<b><u> WORKED EXAMPLE 1 : </u></b> <br>\nShow that the equation Power = Force X Velocity is homogenous in both its SI Units and Basic Dimensions.\n<br><br>\n<b><u> SOLUTION : </u></b><br>\nGiven equaltion is P= F X v<br>\nWe know <br>\nP= [M][L]<sup>2</sup>[T]<sup>-3</sup><br>\nF= [M][L][T]<sup>-2</sup><br>\nv= [L][T]<sup>-1</sup><br>\nSo the equation becomes<br>\n[M][L]<sup>2</sup>[T]<sup>-3</sup> = [M][L][T]<sup>-2</sup>  X  [L][T]<sup>-1</sup> = [M][L]<sup>2</sup>[T]<sup>-3</sup><br>\n\nSo the equation is dimensionally homogenous.\n\n</html>");
        jLabel9.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
