        jLabel28.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12));
        jLabel28.setText("<html>\n<b>Vectors :</b> The quantities which have magnitude as well as direction and obeys\nvector laws of addition, multiplication etc.<br><br>\n\n<b> Addition of Vectors </b><br>\n(i) Only vectors of same nature can be added.<br>\n(ii) The addition of two vector A and B is resultant R<br>\n <center><b>R</b> = <b>A</b>+<b>B</b><br></center>\n<br>\nAnd R = ( A<sup>2</sup>+ B<sup>2</sup>+ 2AB CosΘ)<sup>1/2</sup><br>\nAnd tan β = B SinΘ/ ( A + B CosΘ) ,<br>\nWhere Θ is the angle between vector A and vector B, And β is the angle which R\nmakes with the direction of A.<br><br>\n(iii) Vector addition is commutative and associative.\n<br><br>\n<b>Dot product or scalar product :</b>The dot product of two vectors A and B,\n is equal to the product of the magnitudes of\nA and B and the Cosine of the smaller angle between them.<br>\nIf Θ is the smaller angle between A and B, then<br>\n  <center><b>A</b> . <b>B</b> = AB CosΘ<br><br> </center>\n<b> Cross Product or Vector Product:</b>The product of the magnitudes of A and B and the sine of the smaller\nangle between them.\nIf Θ is the smaller angle between A and B, then<br>\n <center><b>A</b> X <b>B</b> = AB Sinθ  </center>\n</html>\n");
        jLabel28.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        jLabel28.setBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createTitledBorder(null, "Vectors", javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_JUSTIFICATION, javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_POSITION, new java.awt.Font("AR CENA", 0, 24))); // NOI18N
        jPanel3.add(jLabel28, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(700, 20, 260, 580));

